Lower denoise values need less steps:
Point this to a local folder of style_images
You can optionally set a denoising mask for partial denoising (video inpainting).
For some control modes like depth, it can help to only enforce high values and give the background more freedom!
This entire group encodes all style images into separate IP-adapters that are mapped into the output video using the animated masks above.
Differential Diffusion allows for gradient noise masks to correctly affect eg denoise etc
Extend_Sequence ensures we match the target n_frames, even with an input that is less n_frames or just a single image.
